{"tid":2456192,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"前發言人指特朗普數月內將自設新社交媒體　料用家千萬計","createTime":"2021-03-21T17:11:19.000Z","updateTime":"2021-03-22T02:30:49.000Z","uid":212249,"like":27,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":9,"replies":[{"pid":"71c1763b88c07510625425c1f44dde6289c83444","tid":2456192,"uid":212249,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-03-21T17:11:19.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://cdn.thestandnews.com/media/photos/cache/dt-05_NZwzT_1200x0.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thestandnews.com%2Fmedia%2Fphotos%2Fcache%2Fdt-05_NZwzT_1200x0.png&h=81708e35&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n霍士新聞報道，美國前總統特朗普 2020 年競選時的顧問 Jason Miller 指，特朗普將於未來兩三個月內，以自己建立的社交媒體平台重返網路輿論。<br />\n<br />\nMiller 又表示，該社交媒體將會甚具革命性 (completely redefine the game)，預料將吸引有以千萬計用家。<br />\n<br />\n特朗普過去活躍於 twitter，但其帳號被指涉煽動民眾於今年 1 月衝擊國會。同月，twitter 宣布終止其 @realDonaldTrump 的帳號，「以避免鼓動更大暴力」。特朗普當時已批評 twitter 打擊言論自由，又說早已預料此事會發生，擬探討建立自己平台的可能性。其後 facebook 亦宣布把特朗普的 FB 及 IG 帳號無限期封鎖，現在 facebook 的獨立監督委員會 (Oversight Board) 仍未決定是否會讓他重開帳戶。"},{"pid":"2a6050e0658637f4ae5121f8382569db86b089e1","tid":2456192,"uid":212249,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-03-21T17:12:52.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.thestandnews.com/international/%E5%89%8D%E7%99%BC%E8%A8%80%E4%BA%BA%E6%8C%87%E7%89%B9%E6%9C%97%E6%99%AE%E6%95%B8%E6%9C%88%E5%85%A7%E5%B0%87%E8%87%AA%E8%A8%AD%E6%96%B0%E7%A4%BE%E4%BA%A4%E5%AA%92%E9%AB%94-%E6%96%99%E7%94%A8%E5%AE%B6%E5%8D%83%E8%90%AC%E8%A8%88/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thestandnews.com%2Finternational%2F%25E5%2589%258D%25E7%2599%25BC%25E8%25A8%2580%25E4%25BA%25BA%25E6%258C%2587%25E7%2589%25B9%25E6%259C%2597%25E6%2599%25AE%25E6%2595%25B8%25E6%259C%2588%25E5%2585%25A7%25E5%25B0%2587%25E8%2587%25AA%25E8%25A8%25AD%25E6%2596%25B0%25E7%25A4%25BE%25E4%25BA%25A4%25E5%25AA%2592%25E9%25AB%2594-%25E6%2596%2599%25E7%2594%25A8%25E5%25AE%25B6%25E5%258D%2583%25E8%2590%25AC%25E8%25A8%2588%2F&d=Hu0SY4Cx1oodln7cCHpxbSukga04qSQtFI